WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:03.001
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.036 --> 00:04.570
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.107 --> 00:10.009
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:11.344 --> 00:13.311
♪ I'm gonna do what I want
all day! ♪

00:13.346 --> 00:15.914
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:15.949 --> 00:17.849
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:17.884 --> 00:22.287
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:31.684 --> 00:33.952
Ms. Baker: And after your done
with your cards, you know,

00:33.987 --> 00:37.288
you give them to
a special someone you like.

00:37.323 --> 00:38.790
Or it could just
be a friend, too.

00:38.825 --> 00:39.991
No presh.

00:40.026 --> 00:42.293
You guys are young,
and that's, uh --

00:42.328 --> 00:44.329
ugh, that's your Valentine.

00:44.364 --> 00:47.065
It's your day to
appreciate each other.

00:47.100 --> 00:48.800
Hey, Jeff, Jeff.
Look.

00:48.835 --> 00:51.470
He loves love.

00:53.673 --> 00:55.106
I love love.

00:55.141 --> 00:57.742
[ Giggles ]

00:57.777 --> 00:59.344
[ Gasps ]

01:01.014 --> 01:02.647
[ Grunts ]

01:02.682 --> 01:03.781
[ Sighs ]

01:03.816 --> 01:05.483
There, fixed it.

01:05.518 --> 01:06.584
[ Grunting ]

01:06.619 --> 01:08.086
Hey, guys,
keep it down, please.

01:08.121 --> 01:09.154
Ms. Baker!

01:09.189 --> 01:10.922
Who's your Valentime?

01:10.957 --> 01:13.458
Oh, uh,
it's all of you guys.

01:13.493 --> 01:15.827
You guys are
all of my Valentines.

01:15.862 --> 01:17.495
We already
all have Valentimes.

01:17.530 --> 01:20.999
You got to have a real
Valentime, too, like a grown up.

01:21.034 --> 01:23.268
Is it Mr. Reese?

01:23.303 --> 01:25.537
[ Laughter ]
Ms. Baker: Okay, guys, come on.

01:25.572 --> 01:27.372
Is it no one?

01:27.407 --> 01:29.474
All: Ooh!

01:29.509 --> 01:31.476
Who cares if Ms. Baker
doesn't have a boyfriend?

01:31.511 --> 01:33.344
She's fine on her own.
Uh, Chel-- Chelsea.

01:33.379 --> 01:35.547
I see her all the time
at the Fryer's Cinnapuffs.

01:35.582 --> 01:36.781
Almost every week.

01:36.816 --> 01:38.016
We go there after soccer,

01:38.051 --> 01:39.517
and I see Ms. Baker there
all alone.

01:39.552 --> 01:41.452
Thank you.
- Totally by herself,

01:41.487 --> 01:42.954
and she's okay.
- [ Sighs ]

01:42.989 --> 01:44.355
She's just fine.
Hmm.

01:44.390 --> 01:46.224
Come to think of it,
I don't think I've ever seen her

01:46.259 --> 01:47.692
with anybody else before.

01:47.727 --> 01:49.827
Hmm.

01:49.862 --> 01:53.064
Quiet, class.
It's Sumo's turn now.

01:53.099 --> 01:56.000
Uh, I brought this.
I found it.

01:56.035 --> 01:58.203
-[ Gasps ]
-Whoa.

01:58.238 --> 02:01.005
Hmm.
Interesting take, Sumo.

02:01.040 --> 02:02.574
Instead of a normal
journal entry,

02:02.609 --> 02:05.977
you manifest this heartbreaking
meditation on futility.

02:06.012 --> 02:08.413
Yeah, he's really
smashed in there.

02:08.448 --> 02:11.182
You know, I can't help
but be reminded

02:11.217 --> 02:13.851
of T.S. Eliot's
"The Wasteland."

02:13.886 --> 02:22.193
"And I will show you fear
in a handful of dust."

02:22.228 --> 02:24.162
Cool.
- Um, Mr. Mozer,

02:24.197 --> 02:26.598
are we gonna do anything
for Valentine's Day?

02:26.633 --> 02:27.865
Valentine's Day?

02:27.900 --> 02:30.401
It's not Valentine-- oh.

02:30.436 --> 02:31.669
Oh, it is.

02:31.704 --> 02:35.707
Okay, uh, why don't
we just have a discussion

02:35.742 --> 02:38.743
about how maybe we don't need
big greeting-card companies

02:38.778 --> 02:41.713
telling us when we should
and should not express our love,

02:41.748 --> 02:42.847
and through what?

02:42.882 --> 02:44.449
The power of consumerism?

02:44.484 --> 02:47.085
Duncan's mom
made cupcakes.

02:47.120 --> 02:48.386
Oh, cupcakes.

02:48.421 --> 02:51.789
-Mmm, oh.
-Ooh, chocolate.

02:51.824 --> 02:53.758
Mmm.

02:53.793 --> 02:56.294
[ Sighs ]

02:56.329 --> 02:57.629
Hmm?

02:57.664 --> 02:58.630
What?

02:58.665 --> 02:59.964
How'd this get in --
-Ms. Baker!

02:59.999 --> 03:01.132
-Aah!
-Come over for dinner!

03:01.167 --> 03:02.800
Clarence!
What are you doing?

03:02.835 --> 03:04.435
It's Valentime's.

03:04.470 --> 03:06.371
You can't just have
a sad microwave

03:06.406 --> 03:08.039
eat-it-over-the-sink
dinner.

03:08.074 --> 03:09.941
Come to my house instead.

03:09.976 --> 03:11.609
What? No.
- If you come,

03:11.644 --> 03:14.579
you might get hit
by Cupid's arrow.

03:14.614 --> 03:17.048
[ Whispering ] I found
you an amazing man.

03:17.083 --> 03:18.216
What? Who?

03:18.251 --> 03:20.385
Only the most handsomest,
nicest,

03:20.420 --> 03:21.953
rich man you'll ever meet.

03:21.988 --> 03:23.154
[ Sighs ]
Listen, Clarence,

03:23.189 --> 03:24.956
I'm working on myself right now.

03:24.991 --> 03:25.990
When will you be done?

03:26.025 --> 03:27.558
It doesn't work like that.

03:27.593 --> 03:30.128
Will you be done working
in time for dinner tonight?

03:30.163 --> 03:31.496
[ Sighs ]

03:31.531 --> 03:33.731
[ Tires screeching ]
See you tonight!

03:33.766 --> 03:35.099
Come in, Sumo.

03:35.134 --> 03:36.768
[ School bell rings ]

03:36.803 --> 03:38.836
Male voice:<i> And I will show you</i>
<i>something different.</i>

03:38.871 --> 03:41.639
<i>From either your shadow at</i>
<i>morning, striding behind you...</i>

03:41.674 --> 03:42.907
Clarence:
<i>Sumo, do you read me?</i>

03:42.942 --> 03:44.242
What's up, man?

03:44.277 --> 03:46.678
<i>Do you know</i>
<i>of any amazing men?</i>

03:46.713 --> 03:47.845
Uh...

03:47.880 --> 03:50.114
[ Jazz music plays ]

03:50.149 --> 03:53.084
[ Chuckles ]

03:53.119 --> 03:54.352
Ahh --
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:54.387 --> 03:56.854
Huh? Uh, did you
order pizza already?

03:56.889 --> 03:58.189
What? No.

03:58.224 --> 03:59.957
Oh.
Ms. Baker.

03:59.992 --> 04:01.492
I mean, Melanie.

04:01.527 --> 04:03.528
What brings you here?
Is -- is Clarence in trouble?

04:03.563 --> 04:05.596
Mom, Ms. Baker's
coming over for dinner!

04:05.631 --> 04:07.832
Oh, Ms. Baker.
You look great.

04:07.867 --> 04:10.635
Clarence, I thought you were
supposed to be at Sumo's.

04:10.670 --> 04:12.537
Holy smokes.

04:12.572 --> 04:14.372
I did not know we were
having company tonight.

04:14.407 --> 04:16.274
Why is it so dark
in here?

04:16.309 --> 04:17.875
Well, I-I hope
I'm not imposing.

04:17.910 --> 04:19.043
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

04:19.078 --> 04:20.511
Please, come in.

04:20.546 --> 04:23.014
We're just -- we'll just
turn on these darn lights.

04:23.049 --> 04:24.382
[ Laughs ]
- Okay.

04:24.417 --> 04:26.317
Oh, my gosh,
you're in my house.

04:26.352 --> 04:28.286
I'll show you around.
Don't be scared.

04:28.321 --> 04:30.121
It's not so different
from school.

04:30.156 --> 04:32.357
[ Chuckles ]
This is a coffee table.

04:32.392 --> 04:35.526
It's kind of like
a desk, um, but for, like,

04:35.561 --> 04:37.829
watching TV
and putting your feet on.

04:37.864 --> 04:39.564
And this is my TV.

04:39.599 --> 04:43.034
Sometimes I watch it
instead of doing my homework.

04:43.069 --> 04:45.002
Sorry.

04:45.037 --> 04:46.637
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my gosh.

04:46.672 --> 04:49.340
Looks like Mozer got cold feet.

04:49.375 --> 04:51.909
Mr. Chicken to Rooster Boy.
Do you read me?

04:51.944 --> 04:53.211
Cue the backup.

04:53.246 --> 04:56.548
Copy that.
Hey. Come on.

04:57.350 --> 04:58.383
[ Doorbell rings ]

04:58.418 --> 05:00.718
Sumo, abort backup!

05:00.753 --> 05:02.019
<i>Abort! Abort! Abort!</i>

05:02.054 --> 05:05.089
Hey, get out of here.

05:05.124 --> 05:08.893
Your prince has arrived.

05:08.928 --> 05:10.094
[ Sighs ]

05:10.129 --> 05:11.829
[ Hums ]

05:11.864 --> 05:13.064
Hi, Mr. Mozer!

05:13.099 --> 05:14.265
Howdy, Clarence.

05:14.300 --> 05:15.933
Thanks so much
for having me over.

05:15.968 --> 05:20.238
Hey, I heard somebody likes
a certain special TV show.

05:20.273 --> 05:22.740
Clarence: [ Gasps ]
Oh, my gosh, "The Mmms."

05:22.775 --> 05:24.742
You're a perfect man.

05:24.777 --> 05:26.744
Take my hand.

05:26.779 --> 05:28.913
Mr. Mozer, I want you
to meet Ms. Baker.

05:28.948 --> 05:30.348
Oh, hi.
- Oh.

05:30.383 --> 05:31.749
Nice to meet you, yes.
I think I recognize you

05:31.784 --> 05:34.252
from the Common Curriculum
Conference.

05:34.287 --> 05:35.953
Oh, you were there?
- Of course.

05:35.988 --> 05:39.624
I remember you asked
an insightful question about --

05:39.659 --> 05:41.759
Oh, oh, oh, oh.
About those furlough days.

05:41.794 --> 05:43.027
Right!

05:43.062 --> 05:47.565
Everyone was thinking it,
and you just said it!

05:47.600 --> 05:50.201
[ Laughs ] Yeah, well,
what were they thinking?

05:50.236 --> 05:52.303
Sometime you just
got to teach 'em.

05:52.338 --> 05:53.604
[ Both laugh ]

05:53.639 --> 05:55.139
You got to -- you got
to teach them, yeah.

05:55.174 --> 05:57.642
It's working.

05:57.677 --> 05:59.310
[ Sighs ]

05:59.345 --> 06:01.479
Oh, boy. [ Sniffs ]
Ugh, no, that's not good.

06:01.514 --> 06:02.814
Clarence: Okay, Ms. Baker.
You sit over here,

06:02.849 --> 06:05.750
and, Mr. Mozer,
you sit right here.

06:05.785 --> 06:07.785
Oh, yeah, great.
[ Chuckles ]

06:07.820 --> 06:10.922
[ Clears throat ]

06:10.957 --> 06:13.157
[ Chuckles ]

06:13.192 --> 06:15.527
[ Chuckles ]

06:16.329 --> 06:18.129
Ah, kids, right?

06:18.164 --> 06:19.430
[ Laughs ]

06:19.465 --> 06:21.265
Oh, man,
we're in luck.

06:21.300 --> 06:22.934
I found
an extra seat.

06:22.969 --> 06:24.936
So good to have you guys
over for dinner.

06:24.971 --> 06:28.306
I managed to, uh, scrounge
something up for us.

06:28.341 --> 06:29.774
I'm starting to

06:29.809 --> 06:32.143
get the feeling that --
-Drinks for the lady!

06:32.178 --> 06:34.178
Da, da, da, da!

06:34.213 --> 06:35.646
Get a little juice
in here.

06:35.681 --> 06:38.583
So, Mr. Mozer, looks like
you're really hitting it off

06:38.618 --> 06:40.117
with your Valentime's date.

06:40.152 --> 06:41.352
Oh, uh, thank you.

06:41.387 --> 06:43.354
Wait. Date?

06:44.991 --> 06:46.324
Date?

06:48.027 --> 06:49.360
Date?

06:49.395 --> 06:51.996
These drinks
are pretty good, huh?

06:52.031 --> 06:53.998
Date?

06:54.033 --> 06:55.800
[ Bell tolls ]

06:55.835 --> 06:58.970
[ Wailing ]

06:59.005 --> 07:02.006
Date? Date? Date?

07:02.041 --> 07:03.207
Uh, Craig?

07:03.242 --> 07:07.044
Yes! The drinks
are very good!

07:07.079 --> 07:08.279
Oh, wow.

07:08.314 --> 07:10.047
Uh, you know,
you really can't force

07:10.082 --> 07:11.449
these Valentine's things.

07:11.484 --> 07:13.618
It was only when
I really stopped looking,

07:13.653 --> 07:15.620
you know, that I got in
a good enough place

07:15.655 --> 07:17.855
where Chad and I just
found each other naturally.

07:17.890 --> 07:19.490
Huh? Oh, oh, no, no.
We're -- we're not --

07:19.525 --> 07:21.025
No, no, not us.
No.

07:21.060 --> 07:24.462
Oh, it's true, man.
Oh, I love the single life.

07:24.497 --> 07:26.831
Uh, but finding Mary

07:26.866 --> 07:28.866
was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

07:28.901 --> 07:30.801
[ Both chuckle ]

07:30.836 --> 07:32.670
Yeah.

07:32.705 --> 07:34.972
Uh...

07:35.007 --> 07:36.140
Hmm.

07:36.175 --> 07:39.176
Sumo, a word.

07:39.211 --> 07:40.745
Kkk! What are
we gonna do?

07:40.780 --> 07:42.880
Mom and Chad are hogging
all the love.

07:42.915 --> 07:45.349
Uh, on it.

07:45.384 --> 07:46.584
[ Tearing, thud ]
What? Ow!

07:46.619 --> 07:47.652
Mar.

07:47.687 --> 07:49.320
Come on, Chad.
I was just playing.

07:49.355 --> 07:52.557
Kkk! Now we got
to spice things up.

07:52.592 --> 07:54.892
Time for the love potion.

07:54.927 --> 07:56.594
Copy that.

07:56.629 --> 07:59.196
Okay, time to get
to know each other.

07:59.231 --> 08:01.432
Starting with Ms. Baker.

08:01.467 --> 08:04.602
Ms. Baker writes,
"I'm a simple, small-town girl

08:04.637 --> 08:07.505
with big-time,
uh, ambitions."

08:07.540 --> 08:09.073
Is that my
Aber-Dating profile?!

08:09.108 --> 08:12.777
Yep. We found Mr. Mozer's, too,
but his was so boring.

08:12.812 --> 08:16.080
[ Groans ] I can't believe
this is happening.

08:16.115 --> 08:18.783
I love Western-style barbecue.

08:18.818 --> 08:19.884
Oh, I like that.

08:19.919 --> 08:21.586
Oh, Western style's
underrated.

08:21.621 --> 08:24.021
Uh, Clarence, I think that's
enough of that, all right?

08:24.056 --> 08:25.256
[ Chuckles ]

08:25.291 --> 08:27.758
Wait, this other stuff
is also kind of boring.

08:27.793 --> 08:29.193
Give it -- Clarence.
- Hello.

08:29.228 --> 08:30.394
C-Clarence!

08:30.429 --> 08:31.696
Ms. Baker,
I'm trying to read it.

08:31.731 --> 08:33.264
That stuff
is really personal.

08:33.299 --> 08:34.732
Let's see here.

08:34.767 --> 08:36.267
We got biggest fears.

08:36.302 --> 08:37.568
Are you scared
of dying alone?

08:37.603 --> 08:39.270
[ Chuckles ]

08:39.305 --> 08:41.305
[ Clears throat,
clicks tongue ]

08:41.340 --> 08:42.974
[ Gasps ] Hmm.

08:43.009 --> 08:44.308
Oh, my.

08:44.343 --> 08:47.044
It is time for the main course.

08:47.079 --> 08:49.213
-Uh...
-[ Sighs ]

08:49.248 --> 08:50.448
♪ Do, do, do, do, do ♪

08:50.483 --> 08:52.417
Oh, here we go.

08:53.519 --> 08:55.420
[ Grunts ]

08:57.156 --> 08:58.155
Here we go.

08:58.190 --> 09:01.092
-Ms. Baker.
-Oh.

09:01.127 --> 09:04.295
[ Humming ]

09:04.330 --> 09:06.464
Sprinkle this.

09:06.499 --> 09:08.833
Eh, a little more.

09:08.868 --> 09:11.969
Mr. Mozer, can you pass this
to Ms. Baker, please?

09:12.004 --> 09:13.304
Oh, uh, sure.

09:13.339 --> 09:15.139
Ooh, yes, thank you.

09:15.174 --> 09:16.641
Uh, mmm, yummy.

09:16.676 --> 09:18.242
Wow, great concept.

09:18.277 --> 09:19.577
Can't wait to try it.

09:19.612 --> 09:21.012
Oh, Craig, you don't
have to do --

09:21.047 --> 09:23.481
The little guy went through
the trouble, so...

09:23.516 --> 09:25.950
[ Gulps ]

09:25.985 --> 09:27.985
[ Gagging ]

09:28.020 --> 09:29.453
[ Gags ]

09:29.488 --> 09:30.921
[ Spits ]

09:30.956 --> 09:33.758
Ew! Ew! Ew! Ew! Ew! Ew! Ew! Ew!

09:33.793 --> 09:35.426
I'm sorry, Melanie.
Please come back.

09:35.461 --> 09:37.161
-Aah!
-We got to rub some club soda

09:37.196 --> 09:38.663
on that dre--

09:38.698 --> 09:40.264
-I'm sorry, I'm sorry!
-Ms. Baker, I know you're not

09:40.299 --> 09:42.433
at school, but you got
to try and fall in love!

09:42.468 --> 09:43.834
Ugh! I got
to get out of here.

09:43.869 --> 09:46.003
[ Engine starts ]
Uh, you know,

09:46.038 --> 09:47.171
why don't we -- whoa!

09:47.206 --> 09:48.873
-Holy moly!
-Oh!

09:48.908 --> 09:49.840
Craig!

09:49.875 --> 09:52.009
[ Straining ] I'm okay.

09:52.044 --> 09:53.177
Ow.

09:53.212 --> 09:55.713
Oh, boy, I'm really sorry
again about all the --

09:55.748 --> 09:58.015
Please, don't worry.
I think we had a good night.

09:58.050 --> 09:59.116
[ Chuckles ]

09:59.151 --> 10:00.985
Did we?

10:01.020 --> 10:01.952
Okay, bye, guys.

10:01.987 --> 10:03.387
-You have a nice night.
-Bye.

10:03.422 --> 10:05.456
Thanks for coming over.

10:05.491 --> 10:08.292
Uh, Valentine's Day,
right?

10:08.327 --> 10:10.027
[ Laughs ]
Uh, yes.

10:10.062 --> 10:12.530
You know, believe it or not,
I've had worse.

10:12.565 --> 10:14.532
Oh, [chuckles]
so have I.

10:14.567 --> 10:16.867
-What are they saying?
-Words of some sort.

10:16.902 --> 10:19.136
Kiss. Kiss. Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.
Kiss. Kiss. Kiss. Kiss. Kiss.

10:19.171 --> 10:21.138
You know, I'm actually
still kind of hungry.

10:21.173 --> 10:24.308
Uh, want to maybe grab
some falafel as pals?

10:24.343 --> 10:26.510
Love me some falafel.

10:26.545 --> 10:29.547
-Now, where were we?
-[ Laughs ]

10:29.582 --> 10:32.049
Looks like Cupid's arrow
struck again.

10:32.084 --> 10:34.485
But why stop here?

10:34.520 --> 10:37.188
♪ Eat my meaty meat hearts ♪

10:37.223 --> 10:39.924
[ Gasps ]

10:39.959 --> 10:43.694
♪ They'll make you fall in love ♪
- Huh?

10:43.729 --> 10:49.567
♪ My meat hearts
will spread the love so far ♪

10:49.602 --> 10:52.002
[ Crash ]

10:52.037 --> 10:57.742
♪ Can you taste
the love tonight? ♪

10:57.777 --> 11:03.081
♪ My meat hearts will
spread my love tonight ♪

11:04.416 --> 11:06.183
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:07.753 --> 11:09.821
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:11.390 --> 11:13.391
♪ Picking my nose ♪
